description: Skyharbour Resources Ltd., a uranium and thorium exploration company, engages in the acquisition, exploration, and evaluation of mineral properties in Saskatchewan, Canada. The company's flagship project is the Moore Lake Uranium project covering 35,705 hectares located on the eastern portion of the Athabasca Basin. The company was formerly known as Skyharbour Developments, Ltd. and changed its name to Skyharbour Resources Ltd. in October 2002. Skyharbour Resources Ltd. was incorporated in 1970 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Jordan P. Trimble B.Sc., C.F.A., CFA
